There was an explosion at the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation, NNPC pipeline at Ijagemo community, in Ijegun, a Lagos suburb,  this morning, leaving several cars were burnt. The exact cause of the explosion is yet to be ascertained.   Officials of the Lagos State Fire Service are currently battling to contain the situation.  According to reports gathered, the incident was caused by activities of pipeline vandals. The vandals were said to have stormed the pipeline at the early hours of Thursday, breaking a pipeline from where they connected a hose, to siphon the petroleum product, into some trucks. It is not clear how the explosion occured. Fear stricken residents have fled their homes, for fear of possible spread of the fire to their houses.  More details to follow.